Johannesburg Three shoppers were injured during a robbery at a jewellery store at East Rand mall, Ekurhuleni, paramedics said on Thursday. &quot;Upon arrival, paramedics were lead into the store where they found the three patients. The man and two women had sustained minor injuries. The patients were treated for their injuries and thereafter transported to Life Glynwood Hospital for further care.&nbsp;&quot;It is believed that an unknown number of gunmen had entered the store and had assaulted the three patients,&quot; said ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring. There were no other injuries reported at the scene.&nbsp;The police investigation continues. African News Agency